SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYTuesday 10 May S10 V1 Liverpool’s title hopes were handed a massive blow against Tottenham at the weekend but they will be fancied to try and keep up the pressure on Manchester City by winning at Villa Park. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 KV Mechelen vs KAA Gent: Mechelen are on a six match unbeaten run at home. Gent beat Mechelen 1-0 at home on Saturday.M2 Valencia vs Real Betis: Valencia meet Betis again three weeks after losing to them on post-match penalties, in the Spanish Cup final.M3 Maccabi Haifa vs Maccabi Tel Aviv: A home win should ensure for Maccabi Haifa the Israeli league title. Haifa beat Tel Aviv 3-2 when they last hosted them in January.M4 Maccabi Netanya vs Bnei Sakhnin: Maccabi Netanya have scored three goals in each of their last two league games. Bnei Sakhnin have not won in their past 11 clashes against Maccabi Netanya.M5 Granada vs Athletic Bilbao: Granada thrashed Mallorca 6-2 away on Saturday to move out of the LaLiga relegation zone. Bilbao’s last away game was a 3-2 victory at Cadiz.M6 Young Boys Berne vs St Gallen: Young Boys are unbeaten in their past 30 home games against St Gallen, stretching back to 2005.M7 Grimsby Town vs Boreham Wood: Grimsby look certain to secure a place in the promotion playoffs but Boreham Wood must win their last two National Conference games to stand any chance.M8 Bromley vs Altrincham: Bromley have drawn three of their past four home matches. Altrincham have lost three of their past four away assignments.M9 Aston Villa vs Liverpool: Villa have won their last two matches while Liverpool’s title hopes crumbled at the weekend with a home draw against Tottenham.M10 Barcelona vs Celta Vigo: Celta Vigo won at Barcelona last season which was only their second success in 24 past trips to Nou Camp. Suggested permutation: R8.00 2,3 x 1,2 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 1 x 3 x 1